RACE.RACE_TEXT: Jack Clifford S. SACRAMENTO RACE 1 300 Y Dirt CR: 88. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. (Quarter Horses). No nomination Fee. $200 to start. With $20,000 Guaranteed, of which 55% to the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 7% to fourth, 2% to fifth and sixth and 1% to seventh and eighth. (In the event there are fewer than eight starters in this race, any purse monies not awarded will be distributed on a prorated basis to all finishers.) Weight: Three-Year-Olds, 123 lbs.; Older 126 lbs. Closed Saturday, July 15, 2023 with 11 nominations. Preferred by moniesea rned in 2022-2023. (No sex allowance.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: APPROVAL GIVEN broke in a step at the start, responded to urging and vied for the lead in the stretch, took command then drifted out heading to the final yards and held in a drive. IMA SIXY MAN raced close to the early leaders, closed well in the stretch and just missed for the win, while holding for second. MID KNIGHT FLASH hopped at the start and was off a step slowly, made a steady gain in the stretch to come within aim, rallied in deep stretch and missed for second, while getting the nod for third. DOLLYS TALENT chased the early leaders, surged in deep stretch and just missed for the minor awards. ONE FAST GAME vied for the lead in the early stages and weakened in deep stretch. THREE TIMES A LADY broke alertly, vied for the lead in the stretch, could not keep pace in the final stages and altered course behind the drifting winner in deep stretch. BARBAS was off a step slowly and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GORM tracked the decent early pace from the inside, came in a bit tight approaching the turn and waited for racing room entering the bend, found room nearing the quarter pole, took command heading into the stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong pole and drew away under moderate late urging in a good debut. MAJOR TOM lunged at the start and was away a bit slowly, chased from the rear into the turn, drifted out approaching the top of the lane and raced five wide into the stretch, could not make headway on the winner in the final furlong and kept on to be clear in the end for second. THECHIEFHASTRICKS was prominent in the early running and pressed the decent pace between rivals, lost position along the turn, could not keep pace into the stretch and ran on in the final stages to secure third. ANOTHER STRIKE was sent to be forwardly placed leaving the break, disputed the decent pace into the turn, set pressured fractions to the quarter marker, could not match strides with GORM into upper stretch, gave way in the final stages and was outfinished for third. SMUGGLER'S COVE broke alertly and disputed the decent early pace with an inner rival, pressed the pace four wide to the quarter marker, lost ground into upper stretch and tired in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIGHTY MATT tracked the solid pace while saving ground, angled three wide for the drive, responded to urging at mid-stretch and confronted DUMB LUCK nearing the sixteenth-marker, drew to even terms and dueled DUMB LUCK in deep stretch, wore that one down in the final strides and won the nod on the wire to prevail. DUMB LUCK was sent to establish the early lead, showed speed while setting disputed fractions into the turn, dueled with OBVIOUS along the bend, shook free from that rival into upper stretch, was kept to task under firm urging to the sixteenth-marker, dug in when confronted by MIGHTY MATT in deep stretch and just missed for the win, while holding safely for second. INDIANERA was allowed to settle leaving the break and tracked the solid pace from the inside, made a mild advance on the turn, was steered three wide into the stretch and ran evenly to the furlong grounds, found his best stride late and was clear in the end for third. TRABIESO AVELITO chased the solid early pace while outside of a rival, was coaxed four wide into the stretch, closed willingly in the final stages but was unable to make an impact. OBVIOUS was asked to show early speed and was prominent in the early going, confronted DUMB LUCK and pressed inside of that rival into the turn, contested the solid pace to the quarter marker, could not keep pace into the stretch and weakened in the final stages.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MORO FIRST CLASS broke well and vied for the early lead with SAINT HELEN, gained a narrow advantage passing the half mile to run, extended the lead through the turn, came into the stretch leading by comfortable margin and won well under intermittent urging. MADAME CAUSEWAY shied when SAINT HELEN came over after the break, raced close to the pacesetters to the turn, made a mild bid passing the three furlong marker and chased the winner home, was never a threat but finished well clear of the third horse. SAINT HELEN broke inward and dueled early with MORO FIRST CLASS remained close up through the turn then began to struggle to keep up thought the turn and was outfinished for second. CHANTELLE was outrun from the break, was never a factor and trailed throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred)(Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won An Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. Unless Entered For A Claiming Price).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RODRIGOKNOWS was sent to establish the early lead, cleared an inner rival and dictated terms from the rail into the backstretch run, set prompted fractions while well handled to the far turn, held SEA DOG at bay into upper stretch, responded to steady urging in the drive, kept to task while holding a narrow lead to the final sixteenth and gamely lasted for the win. SEA DOG was forwardly placed into the first turn, prompted the early pace while outside of RODRIGOKNOWS, kept close attendance to that rival through decent fractions into the far turn, was set down for the drive and kept pressure on RODRIGOKNOWS to the furlong grounds, was unable to get by the determined winner in the final sixteenth and was denied for the win, while besting the rest. UNCLE WALT settled just off of the decent early pace and saved ground into the backstretch run, advanced along the rail heading to the half-mile pole, saved ground to the quarter marker, angled three wide in upper stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, could not muster the needed late response and was outfinished, while holding safely for third. TRINIDAD was forwardly placed in the early running and stalked outside of the leading pair into the backstretch run, remained within striking distance while three wide nearing the quarter marker, chased in the stretch and lacked a late rally. ACERO settled off of the decent early pace, tracked from the two patch along the backstretch run, was steered four wide into the drive and did not offer a late response.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS IVES was forwardly placed in the early running, raced close to the solid pace heading to the turn, advanced to press BLURSDAY heading to the quarter marker, kept pressure on that rival to mid-stretch, closed determinedly in the late stages, wore down the runner-up in the final stages and won the nod on the wire to prevail. BLURSDAY showed speed leaving the break and assumed command in the early stages, set a fast pace into the turn, was pressed to the quarter marker by MISS IVES, held a narrow lead over that rival into upper stretch, fought back gamely to the final sixteenth, could not hold off the winner in the final strides and bested the rest. CITY GLITTER bumped with QUEEN MOLOTOV leaving the break, was allowed to settle and rated off of the solid early pace, raced outside of rivals into the turn and was roused six wide into the stretch, gained ground at the furlong marker, made a mild late bid but was outfinished in deep stretch and just held for third. TESSA (GB) stalked the solid early pace from a three wide position, gained ground while between rivals and three deep nearing the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch, could not muster the needed response in the final furlong and just missed for third. SEEMS LOGICAL chased the fast early pace while outside of rivals, raced widest into the turn and gained ground nearing the quarter marker, was steered four wide into the stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker and lacked a late rally. QUEEN MOLOTOV bobbled at the start then was jostled by a neighboring rival and was away slowly, recovered to chase the solid pace into the turn, ran in pursuit to the quarter marker, could not keep pace in the drive and tired in the final stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Governor's Cup S. SACRAMENTO RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 96. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. No nomination fee, $350 to enter, an additional $350 to start, or by supplementary nomination of $1,500 (which includes all fees) by close of entries Wednesday, July 19, 2023, with $75,000 Guaranteed, of which $45,000 to the winner, $15,000 to second, $9,000 to third, $4,500 to fourth and $1,500 to fifth. Weight: Three-Year-Olds, 122 lbs. Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners of a sweepstakes in 2023 allowed 2 lbs. Closed Saturday, July 15, 2023 with 21 nominatio ns. High weights preferred. Preference for horses with equal weights will be determined by 2023 non-claiming earnings.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANCERY WAY bobbled leaving the start and was off a bit slowly, recovered to navigate early traffic and assumed command heading to the half-mile marker, showed good speed and set a quick pace to the quarter pole, drew to a clear lead into the drive, was kept to task under moderate urging to the final sixteenth and remained clear to the wire. LEXINGTON HUMOR settled just off of the fast early pace, was well placed while saving ground along the turn, could not match strides with CHANCERY WAY into the stretch, made a mild late bid in the final sixteenth and was up in the final strides to secure second. BLUE WILDCAT took back to stalk the quick early pace, raced outside of rivals into the turn, advanced three wide nearing the quarter marker, could not keep pace with CHANCERY WAY into the stretch, lacked the needed response in the final furlong and was just edged for second, while clear for third. MISS UNION broke alertly, ceded the early lead and was allowed to settle while not far back heading to the turn, gained a bit of ground while three deep nearing the quarter pole, lost ground into the stretch and did not offer a late rally. DULCE EMMA was crowded a bit at the start and was off a step slowly, lacked speed into the turn, raced widest to the quarter marker and was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker and did not threaten in the final stages. DANCE TO THE MUSIC was prominent in the early going and pressed the quick pace into the turn, lost ground along the bend and chased the pace between rivals to the quarter marker, was outrun into the stretch and gave way in the final stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred)(If A Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive A $10,000 Ince ntive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN PRAYER broke well, easily gained the early advantage, opened up a clear lead going into the turn while well in hand, quickened away when asked at the top of the stretch and cruised home the easiest of winners. SURFLINE was hard to load, came away well at the start chased GOLDEN PRAYER to the turn, had to be asked to keep pace with that one from the five sixteenths pole and was unable to match strides with that rival but ran on well and was well clear of the third horse. REALLY SATISFYING broke out and made contact with RAY TAYLORS RUMBLE then was outrun early, launched a bid with about three furlongs to run, floated a bit wide into the turn, was not able to impact the top two in the stretch and held clearly for third. LITTLE CHEYENNE hopped at the start, trailed early, made a mild mid-race move but flattened out in the stretch. SOUTHERN BLESSING was pushed to keep pace early, raced close up to the turn, came under pressure with three furlongs to run and had nothing to offer for the stretch run. RAY TAYLORS RUMBLE came away casually from the gate, struggled to keep up with the field heading into the turn, was outrun from there and not persevered with down the stretch.
